title: Carlos Salzedo: From Aeolian to Thunder - Paperbound (LHS)
description: The first comprehensive biography of Carlos Salzedo's remarkable life as a harpist teacher composer and innovator. This book includes listings of Salzedo's original works transcriptions of familiar melodies and his works in manuscript. Published by Lyon & Healy.

title: Marcel Grandjany: Concert Harpist Composer & Teacher
description: Through this collection of biographical sketches reviews and excerpts from fellow artists we gain insight into the personality of the highly acclaimed harpist Marcel Grandjany. Illustrated throughout with black and white photographs and music this insightful book provides a fascinating glimpse into the musical career and method of Grandjany.

title: The Pocket Guide to Harp Composing
description: The Pocket Guide to Harp Composing Composer/Author: REES-ROHRBACHER, D. The Pocket Guide to Harp Composing A concise non-technical manual that covers composing for pedal and lever harp in easy to understand terms.
